      "content": [
        {
          "type": "title",
          "value": "Advanced Particles"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Particles are the soul of Cantonese. They add emotional nuance that is often hard to translate directly."
        },
        {
          "type": "title",
          "value": "zaa3: Only / Just"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Use <strong>咋</strong> (zaa3) to emphasize that something is 'only' or 'just' a certain amount or state."
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "兩個人咋",
          "romanization": "loeng5 go3 jan4 zaa3",
          "translation": "Only two people"
        },
        {
          "type": "title",
          "value": "gwaa3: Uncertainty"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Use <strong>啩</strong> (gwaa3) when you think something is true but aren't 100% sure. It's like saying 'I guess' or 'I suppose'."
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "係啩",
          "romanization": "hai6 gwaa3",
          "translation": "I suppose so / Probably"
        },
        {
          "type": "title",
          "value": "bo3: Realization / Warning"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Use <strong>噃</strong> (bo3) to indicate a new realization, a mild warning, or to draw attention to a fact."
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "好噃",
          "romanization": "hou2 bo3",
          "translation": "That's good! (expressing a positive realization)"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "reading",
      "exerciseId": "5.5.2"
    },
    {
      "type": "unscramble",
      "exerciseId": "5.5.3"
    },
